msContents.summary: Appears to be a fair copy of lecture notes on obstetrics. The unidentified author cites as authorities Smellie, Ould, Heister, Watts, Cadogan, and others. Particular cases described are from London or elsewhere in England.

msItem.title: Of the rise and progress of the obstetric art

supportDesc.extent: 218 leaves : 208 x 126 (174 x 100) mm. bound to 215 x 140 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, ii (modern paper) + 218 + ii (modern paper); [1-218]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by a single hand.

binding.p: Modern quarter leather. Old water damage on the margins of the leaves; leaves are brittle, a few are torn.

origin.p: Probably written in England, in the last quarter of the 18th century (the latest authors cited were published in the 1770s).

history.provenance: Formerly owned by the Mercantile Library, Philadelphia (stamp, f. 2r).
Sold by Philadelphia Rare Books and Manuscripts, 1999.
